{
  "texts": [
    "In all studies, ANI-1xnr closely matches experiment (when available) and/or previous studies using traditional model chemistry methods.",
    "As such, ANI-1xnr proves to be a highly general reactive MLIP for C, H, N and O elements in the condensed phase, enabling high-throughput in silico reactive c he mi stry e xp er im en ta tion.",
    "Over the past several decades, atomic-scale simulation has become an invaluable computational tool for providing microscopic explanations of experimentally observed phenomena.",
    "Many scientifically crucial chemical and materials properties can be evaluated through molecular dynamics (MD) simulation, wherein atomic motion is dictated by integrating the second law of Newtonian physics.",
    "The quantitative predictiveness of MD depends almost entirely on the accuracy of the underlying model potential energy surface (the potential) used to compute the forces acting on each atom."
  ]
}